Description: Limestone amulet in the form of a one-sided right wedjat-eye, pierced lengthwise. The eye is smoothly carved in shallow sunken relief and a series of nicks on the upper edge evokes a corded design.
Curator's comments: Provenance not specified in the Museum register, but probably from Tell Nabasha, according to the context of the item in the list. The shape and size match with Petrie 1888, pl. I, 27 Parallels: Cl. Muller-Winkler, p. 43, 145-146, pl. vii, no. 143.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (pl. I, 27)
